{{About|the present [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] village in [[Tubas Governorate]] of the [[West Bank]]|former Palestinian village in Safad Sub-district |Al-Ras al-Ahmar}} {{Infobox Palestinian Authority municipality |name=Khirbet ar-Ras al-Ahmar |image= |caption= |arname=خربة الراس الاحمر |meaning= |founded= |type= |typefrom= |altOffSp= |altUnoSp= |governorate=tb |coordinates = {{coord|32|16|21|N|35|29|36|E|region:PS|display=inline,title}} |palgrid=196/186 |population=195 |popyear=2010 |area= |areakm= |mayor= }}
'''Khirbet ar-Ras al-Ahmar''' is a small [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] village in the [[Tubas Governorate]] of the [[West Bank]]. The village is located in [[West Bank Areas in the Oslo II Accord|Area C]] of the West Bank, and Israel has designated it a closed military zone for weapons training.<ref>{{cite news|last=McCarthy|first=Rory|date=15 June 2009|title=Report highlights increasing Israeli demolitions of Palestinian homes |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/jun/15/israeli-demolitions-palestinian-homes |newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate= 13 February 2014}}</ref> As of mid-2010, the village had 195 residents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcbs.gov.ps/Portals/_PCBS/Downloads/book1743.pdf|title=Tubas Governorate Statistical Yearbook No. 3|publisher=Palestinian Central Bureau of Statistics |date=April 2011|page=54}}</ref>
