[[File:Road sign in Friulian.jpg|thumb|A bilingual street sign in Italian and Friulian]] [[File:Cartei stradai bilengai.jpg|thumb|Bilingual road sign (Italian and Friulian) near San Vito al Torre]] This is a list in both [[Italian language|Italian]] and [[Friulian language]] of [[Toponym|place names]] in the historical area of [[Friuli]], [[Italy]], with the official spelling standard published by ARLeF - Regional Agency for the Friulian Language in 2009. [[Grave accent]]s ( ` ) on the Friulian forms are to show syllable stress but are rarely written except when placed on the ultimate syllable. Italics are used for the names of municipalities that are not included within the area subject to protection of the Friulian language minority. These names are divided according to the modern Italian [[Provinces of Italy|province]] in which they lie. From the historical point of view, both the Italian and Friulian forms are found in medieval documents. In some cases, though, Italian names were created by the [[Italian fascism|fascist]] regime to Italianise the region.
