{{short description|Water-filled cave in Budapest, Hungary}}

The '''Molnár János Cave''' is a [[thermokarst]]ic water-filled cave system. It is located in the [[Rózsadomb|Rózsadomb district]] of [[Budapest]] in [[Hungary]].<ref name=Suranyi>{{cite journal |last1=Surányi |first1=Gergely |last2=Dombrádi |first2=Endre |last3=Leél-Össy |first3=Szabolcs |year=2010 |title=Contributions of geophysical techniques to the exploration of the Molnár János Cave (Budapest, Hungary) |journal=Acta Carsologica |volume=39 |issue=3 |pages=565–576 |publisher= Slovenian Academy Of Sciences and Arts |issn=0583-6050 |url=http://carsologica.zrc-sazu.si/downloads/393/Suranyi.pdf |accessdate=25 June 2013}}</ref>

The deepest sections reach {{convert|100|m|ft}}, while the total length of explored sections is currently {{convert|5.5|km|mi}}. Cave mouth  is just {{convert|200|m|ft}} from [[river Danube|Danube]]<ref name=Suranyi/>

In 2008, a cave lake was found there, with largest chamber roughly {{convert|86|m|ft}} long, {{convert|27|m|ft}} wide and {{convert|15|m|ft}} high.<ref>[http://www.mjcave.hu/en/cave The    Molnár János Cave].</ref>

