A '''sealed road''' is a road of which the surface has been permanently sealed by the use of one of several pavement treatments, often of composite construction. In some countries, such as [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]], this surface is generically referred to as "seal".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://colouredtarmac.townsquarebangkok.com |title= Tarmac Surface Treatments |publisher= Maria Sherry |accessdate=September 24, 2013}}</ref>
Surface treatments used on sealed roads include: *[[Asphalt concrete]] *[[Chipseal]] *[[Tarmacadam|Tarmac]] *[[Bitumen]]
